<P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/urexron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rexron</A> at: 4/20/01 4:45:05 pm</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#dcdeed><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umaylith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>maylith</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>1</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>4/26/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>8:05:56 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Spell selection</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Spell Selection at level 28 while in groups<br>
<br>
1) Healing<br>
2) Utiliy (load buff needed, STR like Earth, Barbcoat, Wolf Form etc...<br>
3) Skin Like Steel<br>
4) SOW<br>
5) Shield of Barbs<br>
6) Carless Lightning<br>
7) Creeping Crud<br>
8  Snare<br>
<br>
If you have a group worth its salt, combat can usually consist of Snare, Shield of Barbs on tank, Crud then med...if fight lasts long enough you can toss a lightning.  <br>
<br>
Always keep Barbcoat on yourself.  Skin Like Steel is a bit of a mana hog, so don't cast it on everyone at once.  Str like Earth for those that request it....doesn't take a ton of mana.  Wolf form lasts a long time (outdoors of course), and increases your ATTK for those times when the mob has turned and you want to work on your fabulous combat skills.<br>
<br>
Depending on how much WIS you have, the Healing Spell should take between 1/3 and 1/2 of a mana bubble.  You will definatly be looking forward to GH by 28, but you CAN the only healer in a group, you just have to use Crud less and med more and REALLY watch the other health bars.<br>
<br>
SOW is on the list cause most group members at this level still want SOW, plus depending on where you fight you may get requests, I actually like to SOW people when asked and keep it memmed.<br>
<br>
I just turned 29, and am learning what the new spells do for me....more notes later maybe<br>
<br>
<br>
</font><P><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umaylith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>maylith</A> at: 4/26/01 8:33:05 am</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#989dca><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/urexron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rexron</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>The Pie Guy </FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>100</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>4/26/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>12:01:57 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Spell selection</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Thanks for posting Maylith!<br>
<br>
I'd like to offer a few sugguestions.  You can ignore me, I'm not that good at the game.<br>
<br>
Careless lighting is not your best DD.  I believe Combust is what you get at 29.<br>
However, you have 2 spell gems I am going to recommend getting rid of during a group or fighting in general, so you can mem both. if you'd like.<br>
<br>
Also, SoW has a halfway decent duration time.  My sugguestion is when you group, hit yourself then each party member (F2-F6 one by one) and then get rid of it.  Load a better spell that will help more in combat.  At your level, SoW lasts ATLEAST 1/2 an hour.  Same thing with the Skin buff.  Buffs are basically to be loaded, cast, and taken off.  Also, if you are prime buffer (Ie, you dont have a cleric or shammy in your group), always buff your main tank, yourself of course, and if oyu have one, your enchanter.  Your tank with more HP is a tank that can . well .. tank :)  You are main buffer means you are main healer, you will pull aggro sometimes when you heal, you dont want to die.  Chanters are crowd control.  I learned very early on that a dead chanter can often mean a dead party.<br>
<br>
I sugguest Immolate (also level 29, if not 29 yet, use Flamelick).  Those are the same "LINE", and are both not only DoTs (Damage over time) but small Debuffs.  awesome spell that stacks with the Crud/Swarm line!!<br>
<br>
You can then add either another Direct Damage spell, such as Carless Lightning and Combust, or my personal favorite, Root.  I have not taken root off my spell gem since level 5.  First, I dont like chasing monsters.  Even though snare will stop them when you've gotten them down low, some run before they get to that point.  Second, when travelling the world, often times the monsters you encounter dont appreciate you wandering their paths.  I find a root and run technique to be appropriate.  I believe the term is "Ghetto Messing" .. hehe<br>
<br>
Thanks again for your input ... if you come across something I missed, or want to tell me how my changes got you killed, please feel free :)   Also, glad to hear you're grouping instead of soloing =)  Soloing has it's place, but I prefer to group.<br>
